---
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro'
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---
<Layout title="ChatGPT SEO – Complete UK Guide | Rank4AI" description="How to get your business recommended by ChatGPT. ChatGPT SEO guide for UK businesses from Rank4AI.">
<section class="pt-12 pb-24 reveal">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Learn', href: '/learn/' },
      { label: 'Guides', href: '/learn/guides/' },
      { label: 'Chatgpt Seo' }
    ]} />

    <p class="section-tag">Guide</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">ChatGPT SEO – Complete UK Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT has 900+ million weekly active users. When someone asks it to recommend a business in your category, it either mentions you or it does not. There is no page 2.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT's primary web retrieval index is Bing. This means building in the Microsoft and Bing ecosystem is the most direct ChatGPT visibility strategy available. Businesses not submitted to Bing are invisible to ChatGPT web search.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">How ChatGPT Decides Who to Recommend</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">ChatGPT does not rank pages. It interprets entities. It builds a probabilistic model of what your business is, what it specialises in, and how confidently it can recommend you.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The key factors: Bing-indexed content, consistent entity description across multiple sources, structured data, independent citations from trusted sources, and stable positioning over time.</p>
    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What to Do</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Submit to Bing</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">If your site is not in Bing Webmaster Tools, ChatGPT cannot find you via web search.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Build LinkedIn presence</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">LinkedIn has a direct data relationship with Microsoft. Copilot weights LinkedIn presence more heavily than any other platform.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Consistent entity description</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">The same clear description of your business everywhere it appears online. Different descriptions create uncertainty.</p></div>
      <div class="card-teal-border"><h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Independent citations</h3><p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Directories, review platforms, press mentions, editorial coverage. One voice is weak evidence. Many consistent voices are strong evidence.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="bg-off-white border-t border-border text-center py-16 px-10 mt-16">
    <h2 class="!text-2xl mb-4">Check your ChatGPT visibility</h2>
    <a href="/free-audit/" class="cta-primary">Get a Free AI Search Visibility Audit &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
